Description: Handle of Rhodian pottery transport amphora. Rectangular stamp
Curator's comments: Only known from Petrie's drawing in his Journal, 1884-5, p.102, 18. From the same die as Alexandria, Greco-Roman Museum, ABC 0144.42. Name, Ieron.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.0872)
